'''WYCIWYG''' is an [[acronym]] for <i>'''W'''hat '''Y'''ou '''C'''lick '''I'''s '''W'''hat '''Y'''ou '''G'''et</i>. '''WYCIWYG''' means that when a trader clicks on a price, that price is “captured” as the execution price and therefore even if the market moves subsequently, the customer still gets the price he chose, always. '''WYCIWYG''' execution erases all slippage from trading activities.

Abbreviation derived from, but unrelated to, [[WYSIWYG]].

See '''ACM Forex Trading''' website: '''www.ac-markets.com'''

